{"post_content":"<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 1 \u2013 Ansible Fundamentals<\/strong><\/h2>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 1: Course Overview &amp; Ansible Introduction<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What is Ansible?<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The role of Ansible in automation and DevOps<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Agentless architecture vs. other configuration management tools<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Lab setup<\/strong> (installing Ansible, configuring SSH access)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 2: Ansible Architecture &amp; Design<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>How Ansible works<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Control node vs. managed nodes<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The Ansible command-line tool (<code>ansible<\/code>, <code>ansible-playbook<\/code>, <code>ansible-doc<\/code>)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Configuring Ansible (<code>ansible.cfg<\/code>, inventory files)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Managing inventories (static vs. dynamic)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Working with Ansible modules<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Running simple ad-hoc Ansible commands<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 3: Ansible Playbooks \u2013 Introduction<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Introduction to YAML syntax<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Understanding playbook structure (tasks, handlers, plays)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Variables and facts<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Using Jinja2 for templating<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Playbook creation and execution<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Writing and running basic playbooks<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n<!-- \/wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 2 \u2013 Advanced Ansible &amp; Best Practices<\/strong><\/h2>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 4: Ansible Playbooks \u2013 Deep Dive<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Understanding playbook modules (file, service, package, etc.)<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Using <code>register<\/code> to capture command output<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Conditional execution with <code>when<\/code><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Using loops to repeat tasks<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Creating advanced playbooks with conditions and loops<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 5: Structuring Ansible Playbooks<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Why structure matters<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Using <strong>roles<\/strong> to organize playbooks<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Exploring <strong>Ansible Galaxy<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Hands-on: <strong>Creating reusable roles for efficient automation<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 6: Troubleshooting &amp; Best Practices<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Common issues and how to debug<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Using <code>ansible-playbook --check<\/code> and <code>--diff<\/code><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Log management and error handling<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Best practices for maintainable playbooks<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Module 7: Advanced Ansible Techniques<\/strong><\/h3>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Includes &amp; imports for modular playbooks<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Using tags to run specific tasks<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Dynamic inventories for cloud environments<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Managing execution with asynchronous, serial, and parallel processing<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Organizing tasks with blocks<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Securing secrets with <strong>Ansible Vault<\/strong><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Task delegation and magic varia